# ADHD To-Do Desktop App вЂ” Implementation Plan

## Context
Build a brand-new Electron desktop to-do app for a user with ADHD. The app must be dark-mode only, persist data via SQLite, live in the system tray, and include ADHD-friendly features: large live clock, "DO BEFORE 5PM" countdown, focus mode, Pomodoro timer (4Г—25/5 + 30min break), brain dump quick-add, subtasks with time estimates, drag-to-reorder, color coding, and recurring tasks. A gamification research agent is running in the background; its findings will be implemented in a follow-up session.

## Tech Stack
- **Electron** + **electron-vite** (scaffolded via `npm create @quick-start/electron`)
- **React 18** + **TypeScript** (renderer)
- **Tailwind CSS** + **shadcn/ui** (dark UI components)
- **better-sqlite3** (SQLite; native addon, requires `electron-rebuild`)
- **@dnd-kit** (drag-and-drop)
- **date-fns** (date math in both processes)
- **Zustand** (ephemeral UI state only вЂ” not persisted task data)

